  "_notes": "Shokz OpenSwim Pro (bone-conduction, waterproof, open-ear), MAC a0:0c:e2:49:22:05, Company ID 0x0cac (Shenzhen Shokz Co.,Ltd.). Dual-mode device: Bluetooth audio + internal MP3 player (storage). Mode switch via cmd_id=0x25. Control protocol: proprietary binary TLV (shokz_v1) over RFCOMM SPP (UUID 00001101). Observed L2CAP: CID 0x0050 host->device, CID 0x0057 device->host, CID 0x0076 AVRCP PassThrough. Two top-level packet formats: FORMAT A = persistent settings (prefix 53ff, tail 2d); FORMAT B = immediate actions (prefix 53ef, tail 31). The sequence byte at offset 2 appears to be a rolling 8-bit counter per RFCOMM session. The 2-byte field at offsets 14-15 in FORMAT A (or 13-14 in FORMAT B) is a per-command checksum or timestamp that varies per packet. AVRCP (PSM 0x0017, CID 0x0076) is also used for standard BT media control — handled natively by Android."
}
